 HN1[
] This section confers broad investigative powers on the commissioner, enabling the production of evidence "on any 
subject touching insurance business."

 HRS § 443-23 states that: A licensee shall not collect, or attempt to collect, any collection fee or attorney's fee or commission from any debtor; 
provided, however, attorney's fee or commission may be collected after filing of a suit against any debtor and such fee or 
commission shall not be in excess of twenty-five per cent of the unpaid principal balance.

